
---
import ChecklistItem from '../ChecklistItem.astro';
import InstructionNote from '../InstructionNote.astro';
---
            <!-- Section 7: Documentation -->
            <section id="implementation">
                <h2>Implementation</h2>
                
                <!--- <InstructionNote>
                    List the testing tools your team will use to verify accessibility. Then, construct a pre-flight audit checklist containing the minimum standards an asset must pass before publication, based on the rules you defined above.
                </InstructionNote> -->

                <h3>Approved Accessibility Tools</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>axe DevTools</li>
                    <li>NVDA or VoiceOver</li>
                    <li>Color Contrast Analyzer</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Pre-Flight Audit Checklist</h3>
                <p>Before publishing any digital asset for Red Bull, designers and content creators must verify the following:</p>
                <ul class="checklist">
        <ChecklistItem id="audit1" label="Body text meets 4.5:1 contrast" />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit2" label="Link text meets the minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against the background." />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit3" label="Alt descriptions communicate the essential visual information in a clear, concise way." />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit4" label="Color is not the only method used to communicate meaning, status, or required action." />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit5" label="All video and audio content distributed through Red Bull digital platforms can be accessed in text form." />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit6" label="Headings communicate content hierarchy rather than being used solely for visual styling." />
        <ChecklistItem id="audit7" label="Reading level is 6th to 8th grade." />
                </ul>
            </section>